                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety Airways/30:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Port-of-Spain, Trinidad</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Demorest</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Port-of-Spain</hi>,] <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >Trinidad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-22T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1929—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have been informed by Governor of Trinidad that the Secretary of State for
                    Colonies has granted temporary permission for three Sikorsky aeroplanes
                    belonging to New York, Rio, and Buenos Aires Line Incorporated, subsidiary
                    Tri-Motors Safety Airways Incorporated, to fly over and land in Trinidad. Urgent
                    that line be notified immediately that there are no safe landing places for
                    aeroplanes, extremely dangerous. Only seaplanes or amphibian planes can be
                    used.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Demorest</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
